solutions.content:
**Logic used -**
* perimeter of triangle - summation of sides of triangle (**p = l1 + l2 + l3**)
* Triangle property - In order to create a triangle, largest side is always lesser than the summation of other two sides (**l1 < l2 + l3** considering l1 > l2, l3)

**Explanation -**

1.  we need largest three sides to form a triangle, so better to sort an array.
2.  loop from the last element and pick last three element, if they satisfy the triangle property then return it.
3.  Otherwise no solution found, return 0 


```
class Solution {
    public int largestPerimeter(int[] nums) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int last = nums.length-1;
        while(last-1 > 0){
            if(nums[last] < nums[last-1] + nums[last-2]) // triangle property => largest size < addition of other two sides
                return nums[last] + nums[last-1] + nums[last-2];
            last--;
        }
        return 0;
    }
}
```
TC - O(nlogn)
SC - O(1)
