**Method 1:** Find all 1s and 0s counts, then find max
>**T/S:** O(n)/O(n)
```
public int maxScore(String s) {
	var n = s.length();

	var zeroes = new int[n];
	zeroes[0] = (s.charAt(0) == '0') ? 1 : 0;

	var ones = new int[n];
	ones[n - 1] = (s.charAt(n - 1) == '1') ? 1 : 0;

	for (int i = 1, j = n - 2; i < n; i++, j--) {
		zeroes[i] = zeroes[i - 1] + (s.charAt(i) == '0' ? 1 : 0);
		ones[j] = ones[j + 1] + (s.charAt(j) == '1' ? 1 : 0);
	}

	var maxScore = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
	for (var i = 0; i + 1 < n; i++)
		maxScore = Math.max(maxScore, zeroes[i] + ones[i + 1]);
	return maxScore;
}
```

**Method 2:** Observational
```
Max score = max(left 0s + right 1s)
= max(left 0s + total 1s - left 1s)
= max(left 0s - left 1s) + total 1s
```
>**T/S:** O(n)/O(1)
```
public int maxScore(String s) {
	var ones = 0;
	var maxScore = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

	for (int i = 0, zeros = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
		if (s.charAt(i) == '0')
			zeros++;
		else
			ones++;
		if (i < s.length() - 1) // since we want non-empty partitions
			maxScore = Math.max(maxScore, zeros - ones);
	}

	return maxScore + ones;
}
```
