1. Count the fequency of 1 from s
2. If s[i] is 0 count up it to the variable `zero`.
3. Else if s[i] is 1 count down it to the variable `one`.
4.  Update result if `zero + one` is bigger than previous results.
- Time Complexity: O(n)
- Space Complexity: O(1)
```JavaScript
/**
 * @param {string} s
 * @return {number}
 */
var maxScore = function(s) {
    let zero = 0, one = [...s.matchAll(/1/g)].length, res = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i + 1 < s.length; i++) {
        s[i] === "0" ? zero++ : one--;
        res = Math.max(zero + one, res);
    }
    return res;
};
```

