Split a 0-1 string into two parts, what is the maximum sum of number of zeros in the left part and number of ones in the right part?

# Explanation

Just count the number of 0s and 1s in the whole string, and then calculate the number of 0s in every left substring.

The time complexity is O(n).

# C++ Solution

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int maxScore(string s) {
        int zeroSum = 0, oneSum = 0;
        for (char c: s)
            if (c == '0') zeroSum++;
            else oneSum++;

        int zeros = 0, ones = 0;
        int ans = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length() - 1; i++) {
            if (s[i] == '0') zeros++;
            else ones++;
            ans = max(ans, zeros + oneSum - ones);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

