**IDEA:**
idea is very similar to [Kadanes Algorithm](https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subarray/discuss/1108980/Thought-Process-and-O(N)-java-solution). not exactly same because :
1.nums values are always going to be positive as per constraint. so as in kadane's either we start from ourself or be a part of previous . Here we know that if there exist a previous valid subarray the sum is definately going to be positive. So I am definately going to merge myself into that . no Point of starting from ourself if valid subarray exist.
2.if previous value is greater than me . means No valid subarray is present start from ourself.

Answer can lie in between of the array. 
eg : [12,17,15,13,**10,11,12**,7,4,3]
So we are going to maintain overall maximum and current maximum.
I have write 2 ways to code this problem

**Complexity:**
```
Time  : O(n)
Space : O(1)
```

**Way1:**
```
public int maxAscendingSum(int[] nums) {
        int currentMax=nums[0];
        int overallMax=nums[0];

        for(int i=1;i<nums.length;i++){

            if(nums[i]>nums[i-1]){
                currentMax+=nums[i];
            }else{
                currentMax=nums[i];
            }

            overallMax=Math.max(currentMax,overallMax);
        }
        return overallMax;
    }
```

**Way2:**
```
    public int maxAscendingSum(int[] nums) {
        int currentMax=nums[0];
        int overallMax=nums[0];

        for(int i=1;i<nums.length;i++){

            if(!(nums[i]>nums[i-1])){ 
                currentMax=0;
            }

            currentMax+=nums[i];
            overallMax=Math.max(currentMax,overallMax);
        }
        return overallMax;
  }
```	

**Mistake People Generally Do**:
###### 1. miss boundary Case (what is array length is zero this code will throw error ) [given constraint nums.length>1 so chill] . Confirm this to your interviewer can array length be 0?
###### 2. use concept of LIS(longest increasing subsequence) .. but here **we need subarray** if subsequence is needed then you can use DP concept of LIS.
###### 3. If in interview a this question is asked  to you then make sure you clarify this from interviewer:
###### 3.1 can sum exceed the Integer.MAX_VALUE?
###### 3.2 array contain negative values or not?
###### If you just code it up without clarifying these you may get Rejection even after solving in most optimised way.. 
